-- Peabody Says First-Quarter Sales Will Decline by 2 Million Tons
-- B y   S i m o n   C a s e y
-- 2012-12-14T13:38:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-14/peabody-says-first-quarter-sales-will-decline-by-2-million-tons.html
Peabody Energy Corp. said first-
quarter 2013 coal sales in the U.S. will drop by about 2 million
tons.  U.S. sales volumes will be 180 million to 190 million tons
next year, compared with targeted 2012 sales of 188 million to
192 million tons, the company said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
